Preheat the oven to 220C/200C Fan/Gas 7. Line a large baking tray with baking paper.Combine the butter, garlic, coriander, halloumi and pine nuts in a bowl and season with salt and pepper. Drizzle in the olive oil and mix well.Arrange the mushrooms on the prepared baking tray with their stalks facing upwards.Divide the halloumi mixture between the centres of each mushroom, pressing it into the middle. Roast for 35â€“40 minutes, or until cooked through and serve.